---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Loader from '../../../components/Loader.astro';
import Cursor from '../../../components/Cursor.astro';
import Nav from '../../../components/Nav.astro';
import FsMenu from '../../../components/FsMenu.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import '../../../styles/global.css';
import '../../../styles/stories.css';
---

<Base title="The Waitlist — Basit Masood" description="700,000 signups. Zero ad spend. The gamified pre-launch that made Pakistan desperate to join a neobank that didn't exist yet.">

<script is:inline>
  (function(){
    var apply = function(){ document.body && document.body.classList.add('page-light'); };
    var clear = function(){ document.body && document.body.classList.remove('page-light'); };
    apply();
    document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', apply);
    document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', apply);
    document.addEventListener('astro:before-swap', clear);
  })();
</script>

<Loader />
<Cursor />
<Nav active="stories" />
<FsMenu />

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="sp2-hero">
  <div class="sp2-hero-inner">
    <p class="sp2-hero-eyebrow">
      <a href="/stories/sadapay" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:none;">← SadaPay</a> · Case study · 2021
    </p>
    <h1 class="sp2-hero-primary">Zero ad spend. 700K signups.</h1>
    <p class="sp2-hero-secondary">The waitlist that broke Pakistan's internet.</p>
    <p class="sp2-hero-desc">SadaPay had a bold visual identity, a product vision people could believe in, and zero marketing budget. I designed a gamified waitlist with Founders Club tiers, golden tickets, and branded merchandise that turned the pre-launch into a cultural phenomenon. 700,000 signups. Zero paid acquisition.</p>
  </div>
  <span class="sp2-hero-scroll">Scroll</span>
</section>

<!-- BRAND MOMENT -->
<section class="sb-brand">
  <div class="sb-brand-inner">
    <img src="/images/sadapay-full-logo.svg" alt="SadaPay" class="sb-brand-logo" />
    <div class="sb-brand-rule"></div>
    <p class="sb-brand-caption">SadaPay Waitlist · Pre-launch · 2021</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CHALLENGE -->
<section class="sub-section">
  <div class="sub-section-inner">
    <span class="sub-section-label">Challenge</span>
    <div>
      <h2 class="sub-section-heading">A neobank<br/>that didn't <span class="accent">exist yet</span>.</h2>
      <div class="sub-section-body">
        <p>Pakistan's first neobank wasn't ready to launch. Zero ad budget, no brand recognition, a market where digital banking was barely a concept. The question became: could we make people desperate to join something that didn't exist yet?</p>
        <p>Traditional fintech launches rely on paid acquisition — performance marketing, influencers, billboards. SadaPay had none of that. What we had was a bold identity and the willingness to try something nobody in Pakistan's tech scene had attempted.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- METRIC HIGHLIGHT -->
<section class="sub-highlight">
  <span class="sub-highlight-value">700K+</span>
  <span class="sub-highlight-label">Pre-launch signups with zero paid acquisition</span>
</section>

<!-- APPROACH -->
<section class="sub-section">
  <div class="sub-section-inner">
    <span class="sub-section-label">Approach</span>
    <div>
      <h2 class="sub-section-heading">Exclusivity<br/>as mechanic.</h2>
      <div class="sub-section-body">
        <p>I designed a multi-layered gamification system inspired by the psychology of exclusivity. Sign up, get a position in the queue, move up by referring friends. Founders Club tiers gave early adopters status — distinct visual identities from standard to gold to the ultra-rare platinum. The black edition became a cultural object people referenced by name.</p>
        <p>Golden tickets were the viral engine — randomly distributed, letting holders skip the entire queue. Unpredictability created lottery-like excitement. People shared screenshots on social media, driving more organic signups. Branded merchandise — exclusive to top referrers — turned the waitlist into a status symbol. Hoodies, stickers, card skins. Each piece reinforced the brand.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PULL QUOTE -->
<section class="sub-pullquote">
  <div class="sub-pullquote-mark">&#8220;</div>
  <p class="sub-pullquote-text">The first Pakistani fintech to generate genuine FOMO.</p>
  <p class="sub-pullquote-cite">The SadaPay waitlist, 2021</p>
</section>

<!-- OUTCOME -->
<section class="sub-section">
  <div class="sub-section-inner">
    <span class="sub-section-label">Outcome</span>
    <div>
      <h2 class="sub-section-heading">Celebrities joined<br/>unprompted.</h2>
      <div class="sub-section-body">
        <p>The waitlist became more than a growth hack — it became a cultural phenomenon. Celebrities joined organically. Irfan Junejo, one of Pakistan's biggest YouTubers, visited the office unprompted. People posted their queue positions on Instagram stories. Hoodies and card skins surfaced in the feeds of people who'd never worked in fintech.</p>
        <p>It proved that in a market with no precedent for digital banking hype, the right combination of design, psychology, and brand could create demand out of thin air — without a single rupee of paid acquisition.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- NEXT -->
<section class="sp2-next">
  <div class="sp2-next-back"><a href="/stories/sadapay"><span class="sp2-arrow">←</span> Back to SadaPay</a></div>
  <a href="/stories/sadapay/nukta" class="sp2-next-cta">
    <span class="label">Next Case Study</span>
    <span class="title">Nukta <span class="sp2-arrow">→</span></span>
  </a>
</section>

<Footer />

<script>
  function initSub() {
    const io = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach(e => {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('revealed'); io.unobserve(e.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.08, rootMargin: '0px 0px -40px 0px' });
    document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => io.observe(el));
    if (window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
      document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(el => el.classList.add('revealed'));
    }
  }
  initSub();
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initSub);
</script>

</Base>
